properties.areaDesc: Juneau Borough and Northern Admiralty Island; Salisbury Sound to Cape Fairweather Coastal Area
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 15 at 4:27PM AKST until February 16 at 6:00AM AKST by NWS Juneau AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow. Additional snow accumulations of 2 to 5 inches.

* WHERE...Portions of the central Inner Channels and the eastern
Gulf Coast including Juneau and Pelican.

* WHEN...Until 6 AM AKST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be difficult.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Snow showers are expected to continue
through the night. Temperatures at Pelican are expected to cool
overnight which should allow snow to accumulate more then it has
been. Snowfall amounts will be highly variable due to the
showery nature of the precipitation.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

An advisory means that a potentially hazardous event is already
occurring or imminent.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 AM AKST SUNDAY
